title: Ground News - Wiens, Zsombor-Murray: Canada's best men's diving Olympic medal hopes since Despatie
text:
Summary by Ground News Canadian divers Rylan Wiens and Nathan Zsombor-Murray qualify for 10-metre platform final. Coach Mary Carroll believes they have what it takes to land Canada its first Olympic medal in men's diving since Beijing 2008. Wiens, a 22-year-old from Pike Lake, Sask., and Zsombor-Murray, 20, have already qualified for Paris Olympics . Share menu 6 Articles 6 Articles All Left Center Right
